itemLabel: Conor Myles John O'Brien, 18th Baron Inchiquin

wikipedia_page.main: Conor Myles John O'Brien, 18th Baron Inchiquin (born 17 July 1943) is a British-born holder of an Irish peerage, of the 31st generation in direct descent from Irish High King Brian Boru.  Although the principal Irish residence was sold, he remains a landowner in County Clare.

response: , the titles are held by the 15th Baron Inchiquin's grandson, Conor Myles John O'Brien, 18th Baron Inchiquin, born , who succeeded to the title in 1982 from his uncles Donough O'Brien, 16th Baron Inchiquin and Phaedrig O'Brien, 17th Baron Inchiquin.
